    {
      "heading": "Displaying Physical Values in Binary Format",
      "level": 2,
      "content": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "Example: Signal with Factor and Offset",
          "8 bit signal, signed, with Factor = 2 and Offset = -100",
          "The physical value range is -356..154.Even though the signal consists of only one byte, two bytes are needed for the display.",
          "-128",
          "1000 0000",
          "-356",
          "11111110 10011100",
          "-1",
          "1111 1111",
          "-102",
          "11111111 10011010",
          "100",
          "0110 0100",
          "01100100",
          "127",
          "0111 1111",
          "154",
          "10011010"
        ],
